reviews.review:
Well I have 800 hours in this game and I have a lot of stuff to say.
Been playing since release and the game has evolved and changed a lot for booth better and worse.

Why you should buy/play :
- The thrill of the first 50 hours or so are amazing. You are dropped in a map and you just run around clueless to what to do and you also are terrorized of the killer and what it can do to you. As you play more you start to learn this little tricks and the evolution and the satisfaction of starting to get better is amazing ;
- There are a lot of possibilities to a game and many choices, the fact that you can choose your play style with perks and not only rely on your skill is a good feature and every perk has it's some what counter to make it more fair ;
- The fun you have when you are playing with friends it's so good, especially when one of them is new to the game, every time a friend of mine that is new to the game plays with me it's so funny, although the games end kinda quick, we all end up having fun and doing stupid plays to show off;
- The game developers try to listen to the player base the best they can and did many changes to make the game better for everyone, sure not everyone agrees with me on this but I think that it's not an easy job for them and they are doing great !

Why you should not buy :
- The game has it's issues, hit's from the killer that shouldn't hit, pallets that should have dropped etc., but overall it's not an issue and the developers are working to fix this issues and they did like dead hard and pallet stun hit (Still rough around the edges);
- Some player are sore losers or just like to bully others for the lack of skill. I find this sad and some players are just bad, for example, a player that sat on gens, hid the entire game and escaped, in the end game chat says the killer is trash while he just wasn't that great either. Among other toxic behavior ;
- The new MMR system is not that good, the way it works encourages survivor players to play more solo and not as a team, also you get queued with players and killers that are not truly your MMR and you either loose easily or win easily ;
- Some games you will get unlucky and the killer will just force you out of the game by camping you or chasing you after you get unhooked, this is very discouraging not going to lie, I have quitted the game for some periods of time because of this, but you will get over it and the developers are trying to get a more efficient way to prevent this ;

I still have many more complaints and good things to say about the game, but I fell this is the basic topics for a person that didn't play the game to know and help in the decision of buying the game or not.
I hope this review helps someone and that soon I will be able to play with or against some new player !

P.S the 800 hours are not in this account :)
